  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Come against her from the utmost border,.... Or, \"from the end\" (a); from the end of the earth; from the Persian gulf, and the Caspian sea, on which the Persians and Medes bordered; from the most distant countries; for the Medes and Persians, who are here called unto, brought others along with them in their army from places still more remote; for this is not to be understood, with the Targum, of entering into Babylon on one \"side\"; or, with Jarchi, of beginning at one \"end\" of the city, that it might not be known, and be taken suddenly: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "open her storehouses; where her gold, silver, jewels, and other precious things, lay: or, her barns or \"granaries\" (b), as the Targum and Kimchi; where the fruits and increase of the earth were laid up; and may figuratively design her cities and fortified places, full of inhabitants, as well as of riches and stores of all kinds: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "cast her up as heaps; as heaps of rubbish to make a causeway of, and then tread upon them to make it smooth: or, \"as heaps\", or \"sheaves\" (c) of corn; tread upon them as oxen do, and thereby thresh them out; so Jarchi interprets it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"thresh her as grains of wheat;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to this sense the Targum refers, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"consume her substance as they consume heaps of wheat;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "see Revelation 18:12; ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 18:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and destroy her utterly: let nothing of her be left; of the city of Babylon, its inhabitants, wealth, and riches; so complete should the destruction be, Revelation 18:8. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and destroy her utterly: let nothing of her be left; of the city of Babylon, its inhabitants, wealth, and riches; so complete should the destruction be, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 18:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(a) \"a fine\", Vatablus, Montanus, Schmidt; \"a fine terrae\", Piscator; \"ab extremis finibus\", Tigurine version, Grotius. (b) \"horrea ejus\", Montanus, Cocceius; \"granaria ejus\", Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Schmidt. (c)  \"sicut acervos, sub. tritici\", Vatablus; \"frumenti\", Piscator. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(a) \"a fine\", Vatablus, Montanus, Schmidt; \"a fine terrae\", Piscator; \"ab extremis finibus\", Tigurine version, Grotius. (b) \"horrea ejus\", Montanus, Cocceius; \"granaria ejus\", Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Schmidt. (c)  \"sicut acervos, sub. tritici\", Vatablus; \"frumenti\", Piscator. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
